  "questionId": "gfg-sub-aptitude-geometric-shapes",
  "title": "Geometric Shapes in Maths",
  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Geometric shapes are mathematical figures that represent the forms of objects in the real world. These shapes have defined boundaries, angles, and surfaces, and are fundamental to understanding geometry. Geometric shapes can be categorized into two main types based on their dimensions:</span></p><ol><li value=\"1\"><b><strong>2D Shapes (Two-dimensional shapes)</strong></b><span> \u2013 Shapes with only length and width, lying flat on a plane (e.g., squares, circles).</span></li><li value=\"2\"><b><strong>3D Shapes (Three-dimensional shapes)</strong></b><span> \u2013 Shapes with length, width, and height, giving them volume and depth (e.g., cubes, spheres).</span></li></ol><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Additionally, geometric shapes can be further classified based on their symmetry:</span></p><ul><li value=\"1\"><b><strong>Regular Shapes</strong></b><span>: These are symmetric shapes, where all sides and angles are equal (e.g., squares, equilateral triangles).</span></li><li value=\"2\"><b><strong>Irregular Shapes</strong></b><span>: These shapes lack symmetry and have sides and angles of different lengths and measures (e.g., scalene triangles, freeform shapes).</span></li></ul><gfg-carousel><gfg-carousel-content alt=\"2dshapes.webp\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241212135852322494/2dshapes.webp\" width=\"800\" height=\"400\"></gfg-carousel-content><gfg-carousel-content alt=\"2dreal.webp\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241212135852188811/2dreal.webp\" width=\"800\" height=\"400\"></gfg-carousel-content><gfg-carousel-content alt=\"3dshapes.webp\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241212135852553557/3dshapes.webp\" width=\"800\" height=\"400\"></gfg-carousel-content><gfg-carousel-content alt=\"3dreal.webp\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20241212135852435837/3dreal.webp\" width=\"800\" height=\"400\"></gfg-carousel-content></gfg-carousel><h2 style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Introduction to 2D Shapes</span></h2><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>This section introduces 2D shapes, covering their key properties and classifications, including triangles, squares, circles, and polygons.</span></p><ul><li value=\"1\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/triangles/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Triangle</span></a></li><li value=\"2\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/square/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Square</span></a></li><li value=\"3\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/rectangle/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Rectangle</span></a></li><li value=\"4\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/circles/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Circle</span></a></li><li value=\"5\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/parallelogram/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Parallelogram</span></a></li><li value=\"6\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/rhombus/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Rhombus</span></a></li><li value=\"7\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/trapezium/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Trapezium</span></a></li><li value=\"8\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/pentagon/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Pentagon</span></a></li><li value=\"9\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/hexagon/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Hexagon</span></a></li><li value=\"10\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/heptagon/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Heptagon</span></a></li><li value=\"11\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/octagon/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Octagon</span></a></li><li value=\"12\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/ellipse/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Ellipse</span></a></li><li value=\"13\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/polygon/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Polygons</span></a></li></ul><h2 style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Introduction to 3D Shapes</span></h2><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>This section introduces 3D shapes, covering their key properties and classifications, including cubes, spheres, pyramids, and more.</span></p><ul><li value=\"1\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/cube/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Cube</span></a></li><li value=\"2\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/cuboid-shape-and-properties/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Cuboid</span></a></li><li value=\"3\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/sphere/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Sphere</span></a></li><li value=\"4\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/cylinder/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Cylinder</span></a></li><li value=\"5\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/cone/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Cone</span></a></li><li value=\"6\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/polyhedrons/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Polyhedron</span></a></li><li value=\"7\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/prism/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Prism</span></a></li><li value=\"8\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/pyramid/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Pyramid</span></a></li><li value=\"9\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/hemisphere/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Hemisphere</span></a></li></ul><h3 style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Key Concepts of 2D and 3D Shape</span></h3><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>This section explores the key concepts of 2D and 3D shapes, including how to calculate area and perimeter for 2D shapes, and surface area and volume for 3D shapes. It also covers properties and real-life applications of geometric figures.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-indent: 20px;\"><b><strong>For 2D shapes:</strong></b></p><ul><li value=\"1\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/area-of-2d-shapes/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Area of 2D Shape</span></a></li><li value=\"2\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/perimeter-formulas-for-geometric-shapes/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Perimeter of 2D Shapes</span></a></li></ul><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-indent: 20px;\"><b><strong>For 3D shapes:</strong></b></p><ul><li value=\"1\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/surface-area-formulas/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Surface Area of 3D Shapes</span></a></li><li value=\"2\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/volume-formulas/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Volume of 3D Shapes</span></a></li><li value=\"3\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/properties-and-postulates-of-geometric-figures/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Properties of Geometric Figures</span></a></li><li value=\"4\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/real-life-application-of-3d-shape/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Real-life Applications of 3D shapes</span></a></li></ul><h2 style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Geometry For Programmers</span></h2><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>This section covers geometry for programmers, focusing on geometric algorithms and solving problems like finding the surface area of 3D shapes.</span></p><ul><li value=\"1\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/dsa/geometric-algorithms/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Geometric Algorithms</span></a></li><li value=\"2\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/dsa/getting-started-with-geometry-problems-in-programming/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Getting Started With Geometry Problems in Programming</span></a></li><li value=\"3\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/dsa/find-surface-area-3d-figure/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Find the Surface Area of a 3D Shape</span></a></li></ul>",
